<sect1 id="sec.updater">
 <title>Keeping the System Up-to-date</title>

 <para> &suse; offers a continuous stream of software security patches for
  your product. On your GNOME desktop, the updater informs you about the
  availability of patches and lets you easily install them with just a few
  clicks as described in <xref linkend="sec.updater.gnome.patches"/>. </para>
 <para>Alternatively, you can use the <guimenu>&yast; Online Update</guimenu> to
  install patches. It also offers advanced features to customize the patch
  installation. Please refer to <xref
   linkend="cha.onlineupdate.you"/>
  for more information.
 </para>
 

 <remark condition="clarity">
  2007-08-06 - fs:
  In order to differentiate between official updates and new program versions,
  the official updates are referred to as "patches" contrary to "New (program)
  versions". 
 </remark>

 <sect2 id="sec.updater.gnome">
  <title>The GNOME Updater</title>
  <para>
   Whenever new patches are available, GNOME shows a notification about this on
   the bottom of the desktop (or on the locked screen). <!--Its icon
   changes depending on the availability and relevance of patches and the
   status of the update. -->
  </para>
